Operatives of the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency have arrested the General Overseer of Christ Living Hope Church, Rev. Ugochukwu Ekwem, at the Murtala Muhammed International Airport, Ikeja, Lagos State. A statement on Sunday by the spokesperson for the NDLEA, Femi Babafemi, said the suspect was apprehended on his way to a three-week crusade in Nairobi, Kenya, with 54 sticks of drugs wrapped around his body. Videos of the clergyman preaching has surfaced online. This video has made many Nigerians react in different ways. Read what some of them had to say below, @iam_slimcase wrote, “Daddy freeze is typing.” @harriet_eg wrote, “Omo, know God personally o. Many people are worshipping pastors, and not God.” @wendy_adanma wrote, “Daddy general in action.” @itx_abi_young wrote, “I pity people way carry men of God for head.” POLL @deji_hice wrote, “Our God is indeed a merciful God.” @11thdrip wrote, “Receive maximum frequency.” @asanwa_mummy3 wrote, “If only people will stop patronizing them.”